        "title": "feat(android): localize gateway onboarding",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe Android Node app has no Russian or Hindi runtime resources, and the gateway connection/onboarding flow is English-only.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nMove the highest-value first-run gateway flow onto Android string resources and add Russian/Hindi translations. Add a resource parity check so every locale stays aligned with the English source as the rest of the app is migrated.\n\n## User Impact\n\nAndroid users with Russian or Hindi system locales now get localized gateway connection and onboarding entry points. Unmigrated Android surfaces remain English until follow-up PRs move them to resources.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `pnpm android:i18n:check`\n- `pnpm test:serial test/scripts/android-app-i18n.test.ts test/scripts/native-app-i18n.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt ...`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nThe Android Gradle lint lane could not run because this checkout has no Android SDK configured (`ANDROID_HOME`/`local.properties`).\n\nAI-assisted implementation. This PR is stacked on #97110 so it inherits the native inventory check.\n",
